l\ndecomposition results. For example, we prove that every $n$-vertex tournament\nwhich is $3$-divisible has a triangle decomposition in which the number of\ndirected triangles is less than $0.0222n^2(1+o(1))$ and that every\n$5$-decomposable $n$-vertex graph has a $5$-decomposition in which the fraction\nof cycles of length $5$ is $o_n(1)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 2 Feb 2019 10:14:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-05"}
