0453 B. Conclusions: We conclude that HD\n100453 B has an orbit that is significantly misaligned with the circumprimary\ndisk. Because it is unclear whether such an orbit can explain the observed\nsystem geometry we highlight an alternative scenario that explains all detected\ndisk features where another, (yet) undetected, low mass close companion within\nthe disk cavity, shepherds a misaligned inner disk whose slowly precessing\nshadows excite the spiral arms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 2 Feb 2019 13:55:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-03"}
