m each of the \"four Vs of Big Data\": the sheer Volume of data; the\nVelocity of data arrival; the Variety of forms of data and their origins; and\nthe Veracity of such data. As such, geospatial research has had to adapt to\nharness new forms of data to validly represent real-world phenomena.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 2 Feb 2019 11:26:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-19"}
